				<div class="c-issue-toc__article-collapse-inner">
					<p>In my essay, I set out to posit Warsaw as a Freudian <em>Wunderblock</em> of sorts, inscribing the photographs of its destruction as its ruins proper, as the memory-images that permit it to be read as a spectral city. At the same time, I try to show how one could think of photography - defined as an extension, or supplement of memory - in terms of ruin in its own right.</p>
